title: Phys & Chem Oceanography
description: Study of the dynamics of large-scale ocean circulation, air-sea interaction and their roles in biogeochemical cycling of carbon and nutrients.
restrictions: __HEADER_0__Must be enrolled in one of the following Campuses:
prerequisites: (MATH 1502 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D or MATH 1512 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D or (MATH 1552 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D and (MATH 1553 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D or MATH 1554 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D))) and PHYS 2212 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D and CHEM 1212K Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D
